        <key name="corrector_suggestion_title">Suggestion</key>
        <key name="corrector_suggestion_info">This is a suggestion. To apply it, please change the corresponding setting in the 'Quick Settings' panel.</key>
        <key name="corrector_suggestion_no_change">No text changes are suggested for this item. This is a recommendation to change application settings for the patch to work as intended.</key>
        <key name="corrector_acknowledge_btn">Acknowledge</key>
        <key name="corrector_acknowledged_btn">Acknowledged</key>
        <key name="corrector_enable_scope_btn">Enable Scope Matching</key>
        <key name="corrector_enable_lineno_btn">Enable Precise Patching</key>
        <key name="corrector_feature_enabled_msg_title">Feature Enabled</key>
        <key name="corrector_feature_enabled_msg_text">The required feature has been enabled and saved in Quick Settings.</key>
        <key name="corrector_project_name_error">Invalid format. The project name must be enclosed in angle brackets, e.g., &lt;My Project&gt;</key>
    </section>
    <section name="Tooltips">
        <key name="load_patch_tooltip">Load a .devpatch file from your computer into the editor.</key>
        <key name="examples_tooltip">Browse and load official patch examples.</key>
        <key name="correct_patch_tooltip">Analyze the patch for syntax errors and suggest automatic corrections.</key>
        <key name="check_patch_tooltip">Run a full simulation to check for conflicts and errors before applying.</key>
        <key name="check_code_tooltip">Simulate the patch and then run a syntax check on the modified code.</key>
        <key name="test_run_tooltip">Simulate the patch and then attempt to run the project's launch file to test for runtime errors.</key>
        <key name="execute_patch_tooltip">Execute the full workflow (backup, simulate, apply) to modify the project files.</key>
        <key name="precise_patching_tooltip">Allows using line numbers in the patch for accuracy, which will be removed upon application.</key>
        <key name="fuzzy_matching_tooltip">Searches for the most similar block instead of an exact match. Helps if minor edits were made to the code.</key>
        <key name="scope_matching_tooltip">Restricts the search for the ---old--- block within a larger ---scope--- block, solving the duplicate issue.</key>
        <key name="similarity_threshold_tooltip">Sets the minimum required similarity percentage (1-100) for a fuzzy match to be considered successful.</key>
        <key name="corrector_checkbox_tooltip">Automatically run the patch corrector before simulation and execution.</key>
        <key name="simulation_checkbox_tooltip">Run a dry-run simulation before execution to preview changes and detect conflicts.</key>
        <key name="code_check_checkbox_tooltip">After a successful simulation, check the syntax of the changed files (e.g., Python, JSON).</key>
        <key name="test_run_checkbox_tooltip">After a successful code check, try to launch the project to test for runtime errors.</key>
        <key name="restore_refresh_tooltip">Refresh the list of available backups.</key>
    </section>
</tslang>